[
    {
        "content": "<p>Let's say I defined some function <code>f</code> using <code>def</code> and then I want to prove some theorem which is a property of <code>f</code> and I managed to prove this property for the definition of this function, but in the goal statement the name <code>f</code> appears and not the definition. How can I reach the goal? I tried using <code>dsimp [f]</code>, but  it doesn't work. As a silly example (not the actual thing I'm working on):</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"n\">x</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Continuous</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℝ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↦</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Continuous</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>How would you usually deal with this?</p>",
        "id": 561466937,
        "sender_full_name": "Michael Novak",
        "timestamp": 1764693686
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>unfold f</code></p>",
